Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven
to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Finely dice @tomato{2}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

Place tomatoes in a #medium bowl{}; season with a big pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{pinch}.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @cream cheese{4%tablespoon}, garlic,
3 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4 servings), and a big pinch of salt and pepper. Microwave
for ~{30%seconds}. Stir to combine (you'll use it in the next step).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces,
until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer chicken to a #plate{}, reserving
fat in pan.

Return pan to medium heat. Sprinkle @flour{1%tablespoon} over pan; whisk to
combine. Cook for ~{1%minute}, whisking continuously (a few lumps are okay).
Remove pan from heat. Add cream cheese mixture and whisk until smooth.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Place @flatbreads{2} on a #baking sheet{}; brush tops of each flatbread with a
drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}. Toast on top rack until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, divide between two baking sheets; toast on top and middle racks.

Once flatbreads are toasted, remove from oven. Heat broiler to high or oven to
500 degrees.

Carefully spread sauce over flatbreads; top with seasoned tomatoes to taste
(draining first) and chicken. Massage the @pesto{4%tablespoon} packet for 5
seconds; snip the corner and lightly drizzle flatbreads with pesto to taste.
Evenly sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}.

Broil or bake until cheese melts and flatbreads are golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, broil or bake in batches. Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Allow flatbreads to cool slightly, then slice each into quarters. Serve.